# Plan Management

Plans live in `.cursor/plans/` in the workspace root and must be committed to git.

## When creating a new plan

1. Write the plan to `.cursor/plans/<descriptive-name>.md`
2. Commit it immediately with a message like `"Add <feature> implementation plan."`

## When updating an existing plan

1. **Commit the current state of the plan file first** (so the original is preserved in git history and can be diffed)
2. Then edit the file with the updates
3. Commit the updated version with a message like `"Update <feature> plan: <brief reason>"`

This two-commit approach means every plan revision is diffable in git history.

## File location

- Workspace plans: `I:/CodeProjects/FantasyCritic/.cursor/plans/`
- Cursor-managed plans (in `C:\Users\...\cursor\projects\...\plans\`) are **not** committed — always copy/write to the workspace path above
